com.googlecode.jmxtrans.model.output

Class RRDWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.jmxtrans.model.output.BaseOutputWriter
      • com.googlecode.jmxtrans.model.output.RRDWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OutputWriter, OutputWriterFactory, AutoCloseable

    public class RRDWriter
extends BaseOutputWriter
    This takes a JRobin template.xml file and then creates the database if it doesn't already exist. It will then write the contents of the Query (the Results) to the database. This uses the JRobin rrd format and is incompatible with the C version of rrd.
    Author:
    jon
